<div id="block-pagetitle" class="block block-core block-page-title-block">
          
        
              
  <section  class="hero hero--page">
      <div class="hero__img"></div>
      <div class="grid-container">
          <div class="hero__title">
        <h1>
<span property="schema:name" class="field field--string field--title">Department of Energy Information Quality Guidelines</span>
</h1>
      </div>
    
        </div>
  </section>


              
      </div>
<div data-drupal-messages-fallback class="hidden"></div>
<div id="block-main-page-content" class="block block-system block-system-main-block">
          
        
        
        
      <article about="/cio/department-energy-information-quality-guidelines" typeof="schema:WebPage">

  
      <span property="schema:name" content="Department of Energy Information Quality Guidelines" class="hidden"></span>


  
  <div>
    



  

<section class="layout blade-section--boxed" >

    <div class="grid-container">
      <div class="blade-color blade-section--white" style="">
                                      <div  class="grid-row">
                  <div  class="grid-col">
      

<div class="block block-layout-builder block-inline-blockparagraph-reference layout-align layout-center layout-full layout-width">
        
    
          

            <div class="field field--entity_reference_revisions_entity_view field--field_paragraph_reference field field--name-field-paragraph-reference field--type-entity-reference-revisions field--label-hidden field__item">  <div class="paragraph paragraph--type--blockquote paragraph--view-mode--default">
          
    <div class="blockquote">
      <div class="blockquote-wrapper">
                  <div class="blockquote__quote-text-wrapper">
              <div class="blockquote__quote-text">
                
              </div>
          </div>
        
                  <div class="blockquote__attribution">
            
          </div>
        
              </div>
    </div>
    </div>
</div>
      
            </div>


<div class="block block-layout-builder block-inline-blockbasic">
        
    
          

            <div class="field field--text_default field--body field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden field__item"><h2><strong>Information Quality</strong></h2>

<p>The Department of Energyâ€™s Information Quality Act&nbsp;Guidelines are developed in accordance with Section 515, Treasury and General Government Appropriations Act (Pub.L. 106-554).&nbsp;The law directed the Office of Management and Budget (OMB) to issue government-wide guidelines that "provide policy and procedural guidance to Federal Agencies for ensuring and maximizing the quality, objectivity, utility, and integrity of information (including statistical information) disseminated by Federal Agencies."&nbsp;</p>

<p>OMB guidelines, published in the <em>Federal Register</em> on February 22, 2002 (67 FR 8452), direct agencies to issue their own implementing guidelines that include administrative mechanisms allowing members of the public to seek and obtain correction of information disseminated by the agency that does not comply with OMB or agency guidelines (available at <a aria-label="https://www.whitehouse.gov/wp-content/uploads/legacy_drupal_files/omb/assets/OMB/fedreg/reproducible2.pdf" href="https://www.whitehouse.gov/wp-content/uploads/legacy_drupal_files/omb/assets/OMB/fedreg/reproducible2.pdf" target="_blank" class=" ext">OMB Information Quality Guidelines</a>).&nbsp; On April 24, 2019, OMB further issued Memorandum M-19-15, Improving Implementation of the Information Quality Act, requiring agencies to update their guidelines to address changes in the information landscape and to incorporate best practices developed over time (available at <a aria-label="https://www.whitehouse.gov/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/M-19-15.pdf" href="https://www.whitehouse.gov/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/M-19-15.pdf" target="_blank" class=" ext">Improving Implementation of the Information Quality Act</a>).&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>

<h3><strong>OMB Final Bulletin&nbsp;for Peer Review</strong></h3>

<p>OMB issued a bulletin applicable to all departments and agencies entitled "Final Information Quality Bulletin for Peer Review." This Bulletin establishes government-wide guidance aimed at enhancing the practice of peer review of government science documents. Peer review is an important procedure used to ensure the quality and credibility of published scientific information.&nbsp;This Bulletin is part of an ongoing effort to improve the quality, objectivity, utility, and integrity of scientific information upon which policy decisions are based.&nbsp;<a aria-label="Read more about This guidance emphasizes the benefits of meaningful peer review of science disseminated by the Federal Government" href="https://www.foreffectivegov.org/node/3472" title="Read more about This guidance emphasizes the benefits of meaningful peer review of science disseminated by the Federal Government">This guidance emphasizes the benefits of meaningful peer review of science disseminated by the Federal Government</a><a aria-label="Read more about This guidance emphasizes the benefits of meaningful peer review of science disseminated by the Federal Government." href="https://www.whitehouse.gov/sites/whitehouse.gov/files/omb/assets/OMB/fedreg/2005/011405_peer.pdf" title="Read more about This guidance emphasizes the benefits of meaningful peer review of science disseminated by the Federal Government." target="_blank" class=" ext">.</a></p>

<h3><strong>Department of Energy Information Quality Guidelines</strong></h3>

<p>The Department of Energy (DOE) develops and disseminates information such as factual inputs, data, analyses, technical information, highly influential scientific assessments, and/or influential scientific information.&nbsp;DOE is committed to ensure the array of information it provides to the public is of the highest quality, thus making Information Quality a priority.</p>

<p>DOE's Information Quality Guidelines are intended to provide guidance to Departmental Elements ( <em>i</em>.<em>e</em>., major DOE offices) on; maximizing the quality, objectivity, utility, and integrity of information (including statistical information) disseminated to the public; establish mechanisms for the public to seek and request administrative correction of disseminated information; and explain how the CIO will comply with OMBâ€™s annual reporting requirement concerning complaints from members of the public.&nbsp;</p>

<ul>
	<li><a aria-label="Read more about 2019 Final Updated Version of DOE Information Quality Guidelines" href="/cio/articles/2019-final-updated-version-doe-information-quality-guidelines" title="Read more about 2019 Final Updated Version of DOE Information Quality Guidelines">2019 Final Updated Version of DOE Information Quality Guidelines</a></li>
	<li><a aria-label="Read more about 2002 Version of DOE Information Quality Act Guidelines" href="https://www.energy.gov/sites/prod/files/cioprod/documents/finalinfoqualityguidelines03072011.pdf" title="Read more about 2002 Version of DOE Information Quality Act Guidelines" target="_blank" class=" ext">2002 Version of DOE Information Quality Act Guidelines</a><a aria-label="Read more about 2002 Version of DOE Information Quality Act Guidelines (Archived) " href="https://www.energy.gov/sites/prod/files/cioprod/documents/finalinfoqualityguidelines03072011.pdf" title="Read more about 2002 Version of DOE Information Quality Act Guidelines (Archived) " target="_blank" class=" ext"> (Archived) </a></li>
</ul>

<p>&nbsp;<strong>On this website:</strong></p>

<ul>
	<li><a href="/cio/published-peer-reviews">Published Peer Reviews </a></li>
	<li><a href="/cio/request-correction">How to submit a Request for Correction under the IQA Guidelines&nbsp;</a></li>
	<li>Resolved Requests for Correction
	<ul>
		<li><a aria-label="Read more about Link to IECA/DQA Letter" href="https://cms.doe.gov/cio/downloads/letter-ieca-data-quality-act-request-correction" title="Read more about Link to IECA/DQA Letter">Link to IECA/DQA Letter</a></li>
	</ul>
	</li>
</ul>
</div>
      
            </div>

    </div>
  
        </div>
            </div>
    </div>
  </section>





